'''Luca Antony Jaquez''' (born 2 June 2003) is a Swiss professional footballer who plays as a [[centre-back]] for German {{German football updater|Stuttgart}} club [[VfB Stuttgart]] and the [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]].

==Club career==
Jaquez is a youth product of SC Obergeissenstein, before moving to the youth academy of [[FC Luzern|Luzern]] in 2013. He signed his first professional contract with Luzern on 27 January 2022 until 2025.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://regiofussball.ch/2022/01/27/ardon-jashari-und-luca-jaquez-erhalten-erste-profivertraege/|title=Ardon Jashari und Luca Jaquez erhalten erste Profiverträge|date=27 January 2022}}</ref> He made his professional debut with Luzern in a 3–0 Swiss Super League loss to [[FC Basel|Basel]] on 30 January 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.luzernerzeitung.ch/sport/fcluzern/fussball-toptalent-luca-jaquez-sitzt-oft-auf-der-ersatzbank-warum-spielt-der-fcl-akanji-so-wenig-ld.2517348|title=Toptalent Luca Jaquez sitzt oft auf der Ersatzbank: Warum spielt der FCL-Akanji so wenig?|first=Daniel|last=Wyrsch|date=20 September 2023|website=[[Luzerner Zeitung]]}}</ref> On 24 November 2022, he extended his contract with Luzern until 2026.<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://regiofussball.ch/2022/11/25/luca-jaquez-verlaengert-beim-fc-luzern/|title=Luca Jaquez verlängert beim FC Luzern|date=25 November 2022}}</ref>

On 3 February 2025, Jaquez moved to German club [[VfB Stuttgart]] on a four-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=VfB Stuttgart|url=https://www.vfb.de/en/vfb/latest/news/professionals/2425/vfb-verpflichtet-luca-jaquez/|title=VfB sign Luca Jaquez|date=3 February 2025|access-date=3 February 2025}}</ref>

==International career==
Jaquez was born in Switzerland to a Dominican father and Swiss mother.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.luzernerzeitung.ch/sport/fcluzern/fussball-luca-jaquez-gerade-nur-fcl-bankdruecker-doch-frick-vergleicht-ihn-mit-akanji-ld.2411326|title=Luca Jaquez gerade FCL-Bankdrücker – doch Frick vergleicht ihn mit Akanji|first=Daniel|last=Wyrsch|date=7 February 2023|website=[[Luzerner Zeitung]]}}</ref> He is a youth international for Switzerland, having played for the [[Switzerland national under-20 football team|Switzerland U20]]s in 2022.<ref name="auto"/> He was called up to the senior [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland national team]] for a set of [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group B]] matches in October 2025.<ref>{{cite news |title=Männer-Nationalteam mit vielen Routiniers und zwei Neulingen |url=https://www.football.ch/sfv/nationalteams/a-team/news/maenner-nationalteam-mit-vielen-routiniers-und-zwei-neulingen.aspx |access-date=8 October 2025 |publisher=Schweizerischer Fussballverband |date=2 October 2025 |language=German}}</ref>

